HEADWORD: Stratus
<hw>Stra"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stratus</ets> a spreading out, scattering, from
<ets>sternere</ets>, <ets>stratum</ets>, to spread.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>A form of clouds in which they are arranged in
a horizontal band or layer. See <er>Cloud</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straught</ent>⟦br⟧
